hwAdsl.description: This MIB is used for defining Huawei's ADSL management MIB objects.

hwadslAturChanInfoTable.name: hwadslAturChanInfoTable
hwadslAturChanInfoTable.description: This table provides the channel parameters of the ATUR end of each port. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwadslAturChanInfoEntry.name: hwadslAturChanInfoEntry
hwadslAturChanInfoEntry.description: This table provides the channel parameters of the ATUR end of each port. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwadslAturChanCurrINPInfo.name: hwadslAturChanCurrINPInfo
hwadslAturChanCurrINPInfo.description: Indicates Impulse Noise Protection on upstream direction. The value multiply 1/10000 is the real value. Unit: DMT Symbol

hwadslAturChanRsSymbolsInfo.name: hwadslAturChanRsSymbolsInfo
hwadslAturChanRsSymbolsInfo.description: Indicates Reed-Solomon symbols on upstream direction. The value multiply 1/10000 is the real value. Unit: byte

hwadslAturChanRsRedundancyInfo.name: hwadslAturChanRsRedundancyInfo
hwadslAturChanRsRedundancyInfo.description: Indicates Reed-Solomon redundancy on upstream direction. Unit: byte

hwadslAturChanRsDepthInfo.name: hwadslAturChanRsDepthInfo
hwadslAturChanRsDepthInfo.description: Indicates Reed-Solomon depth on upstream direction. Unit: byte

hwadslAturChanSymbolLengthInfo.name: hwadslAturChanSymbolLengthInfo
hwadslAturChanSymbolLengthInfo.description: Indicates the Bit Number of the DMT Symbol on upstream direction. Unit: bit

hwadslAturChanPhyRrrcBitsInfo.name: hwadslAturChanPhyRrrcBitsInfo
hwadslAturChanPhyRrrcBitsInfo.description: The bits in the channel that used to retransmission on upstream direction.

hwadslAturChanPhyRtxQueueInfo.name: hwadslAturChanPhyRtxQueueInfo
hwadslAturChanPhyRtxQueueInfo.description: Queues in send buffer on upstream direction.

hwadslAturChanRsSizeInfo.name: hwadslAturChanRsSizeInfo
hwadslAturChanRsSizeInfo.description: Indicates Reed-Solomon Codeword Size on upstream direction. Range: 0-255 Unit: byte

hwadslAturChanCodeGainInfo.name: hwadslAturChanCodeGainInfo
hwadslAturChanCodeGainInfo.description: Indicates Code Gain on upstream direction. It ranges from 0 to 16 units of 0.5 dB (physical values are 0 to 8 dB).

hwadslAturChanL2NetDataRate.name: hwadslAturChanL2NetDataRate
hwadslAturChanL2NetDataRate.description: In L2 state, this parameter reports the Net Data Rate in low power state. The data rate is coded in steps of 1000 bit/s.

hwadslAturPhysInfoTable.name: hwadslAturPhysInfoTable
hwadslAturPhysInfoTable.description: This object provides the physical layer parameters of each ATUR. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwadslAturPhysInfoEntry.name: hwadslAturPhysInfoEntry
hwadslAturPhysInfoEntry.description: This object provides the physical layer parameters of each ATUR. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwadslAturTransmissionCapabilitiesInfo.name: hwadslAturTransmissionCapabilitiesInfo
hwadslAturTransmissionCapabilitiesInfo.description: The ATU transmission system capability list of the different coding types. It is coded in a bit-map representation with 1 or more bits set. A bit set to '1' means that the ATU supports the respective coding. The value may be derived from the handshaking procedures defined in G.994.1.

hwAdslAturCurrSignalAtnInfo.name: hwAdslAturCurrSignalAtnInfo
hwAdslAturCurrSignalAtnInfo.description: The signal attenuation value on ATUR: It indicates the difference between the transmit signal of the ATU-C and the receive signal of the ATU-R. Range: 0-630 Unit: tenth dB

hwadslAturInvG994VendorId.name: hwadslAturInvG994VendorId
hwadslAturInvG994VendorId.description: The ATU G.994.1 Vendor ID as inserted in the G.994.1 CL/CLR message. It consists of 8 binary octets, including a country code followed by a (regionally allocated) provider code, as defined in Recommendation T.35.

hwadslAturLInvSelfTestResult.name: hwadslAturLInvSelfTestResult
hwadslAturLInvSelfTestResult.description: The ATU self-test result, coded as a 32-bit value. The most significant octet of the result is '0' if the self-test passed, and '1' if the self-test failed. The interpretation of the other octets is vendor discretionary.

hwadslAtucChanInfoTable.name: hwadslAtucChanInfoTable
hwadslAtucChanInfoTable.description: This object provides the channel parameters of each ATUC. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwadslAtucChanInfoEntry.name: hwadslAtucChanInfoEntry
hwadslAtucChanInfoEntry.description: This object provides the channel parameters of each ATUC. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwadslAtucChanCurrINPInfo.name: hwadslAtucChanCurrINPInfo
hwadslAtucChanCurrINPInfo.description: Indicates Impulse Noise Protection on downstream direction. The value multiply 1/10000 is the real value. If retransmission is used in a given transmit direction, this parameter reports the actual impulse noise protection (INP) against SHINE (under specific conditions detailed in G.998.4) on the bearer channel in the L0 state.In the L2 state, the parameter contains the INP in the previous L0 state. Unit: DMT Symbol

hwadslAtucChanRsSymbolsInfo.name: hwadslAtucChanRsSymbolsInfo
hwadslAtucChanRsSymbolsInfo.description: Indicates Reed-Solomon symbols on downstream direction. The value multiply 1/10000 is the real value. Unit: byte

hwadslAtucChanRsRedundancyInfo.name: hwadslAtucChanRsRedundancyInfo
hwadslAtucChanRsRedundancyInfo.description: Indicates Reed-Solomon redundancy on downstream direction. Unit: byte

hwadslAtucChanRsDepthInfo.name: hwadslAtucChanRsDepthInfo
hwadslAtucChanRsDepthInfo.description: Indicates Reed-Solomon depth on downstream direction. Unit: byte

hwadslAtucChanSymbolLengthInfo.name: hwadslAtucChanSymbolLengthInfo
hwadslAtucChanSymbolLengthInfo.description: Indicates the Bit Number of the DMT Symbol on downstream direction. Unit: bit

hwadslAtucChanPhyRrrcBitsInfo.name: hwadslAtucChanPhyRrrcBitsInfo
hwadslAtucChanPhyRrrcBitsInfo.description: The bits in the channel that used to retransmission on downstream direction.

hwadslAtucChanPhyRtxQueueInfo.name: hwadslAtucChanPhyRtxQueueInfo
hwadslAtucChanPhyRtxQueueInfo.description: Queues in send buffer on downstream direction.

hwadslAtucChanRsSizeInfo.name: hwadslAtucChanRsSizeInfo
hwadslAtucChanRsSizeInfo.description: Indicates Reed-Solomon Codeword Size on downstream direction. Range: 0-255 Unit: byte

hwadslAtucChanCodeGainInfo.name: hwadslAtucChanCodeGainInfo
hwadslAtucChanCodeGainInfo.description: Indicates Code Gain on downstream direction. It ranges from 0 to 16 units of 0.5 dB (physical values are 0 to 8 dB).

hwadslAtucChanPcbInfo.name: hwadslAtucChanPcbInfo
hwadslAtucChanPcbInfo.description: Indicates Power Cut-back on downstream direction. It ranges from 0 to 400 units of 0.1 dB (physical values are 0 to 40 dB) Unit: tenth dB

hwadslAtucChanActNetDataRate.name: hwadslAtucChanActNetDataRate
hwadslAtucChanActNetDataRate.description: Independent whether retransmission is used or not in a given transmit direction: In L0 state, this parameter reports the Net Data Rate (as specified in G.992.3, G.992.5 or G.993.2) at which the bearer channel is operating. In L2 state, the parameter contains the Net Data Rate (as specified in G.992.3, G.992.5 or G.993.2) in the previous L0 state. The data rate is coded in steps of 1000 bit/s.

hwadslAtucChanActINPAgainstREIN.name: hwadslAtucChanActINPAgainstREIN
hwadslAtucChanActINPAgainstREIN.description: If retransmission is used in a given transmit direction, this parameter reports the actual impulse noise protection (INP) against REIN (under specific conditions detailed in G.998.4) on the bearer channel in the L0 state. In the L2 state, the parameter contains the INP in the previous L0 state. The value is coded in fractions of DMT symbols with a granularity of 0.1 symbols.

hwadslAtucChanL2NetDataRate.name: hwadslAtucChanL2NetDataRate
hwadslAtucChanL2NetDataRate.description: In L2 state, this parameter reports the Net Data Rate in low power state. The data rate is coded in steps of 1000 bit/s.

hwadslLineConfProfileCfgTable.name: hwadslLineConfProfileCfgTable
hwadslLineConfProfileCfgTable.description: This table contains information on the ADSL line configuration. The index of this table is adslLineConfProfileName.

hwadslLineConfProfileCfgEntry.name: hwadslLineConfProfileCfgEntry
hwadslLineConfProfileCfgEntry.description: This table contains information on the ADSL line configuration. The index of this entry is adslLineConfProfileName.

hwAdslAtucConfDownBitSwapCfg.name: hwAdslAtucConfDownBitSwapCfg
hwAdslAtucConfDownBitSwapCfg.description: Enables and disables the down bitswap of a template. Options: 1. enabled(1) - Indicates that the downstream bit swap is enabled 2. disabled(2) - Indicates that the downstream bit swap is disabled Default: enabled(1)

hwAdslAtucConfUpBitSwapCfg.name: hwAdslAtucConfUpBitSwapCfg
hwAdslAtucConfUpBitSwapCfg.description: Enables and disables the up bitswap of a template. Options: 1. enabled(1) - Indicates that the upstream bit swap is enabled 2. disabled(2) - Indicates that the upstream bit swap is disabled Default: enabled(1)

hwAdslTrellionsModeEnableCfg.name: hwAdslTrellionsModeEnableCfg
hwAdslTrellionsModeEnableCfg.description: Enables and disables the Trellions mode. Options: 1. enabled(1) - Indicates that the trellis coding is enabled. 2. disabled(2) - Indicates that the trellis coding is disabled. Default: enabled(1)

hwAdslTransmissionModeCfg.name: hwAdslTransmissionModeCfg
hwAdslTransmissionModeCfg.description: Indicates the transmission mode of this channel. Options: 1. all(1) - All (G992.1, G992.2, T1.413)(Default) 2. fullRate(2) - Full rate(G992.1 or T1.413) 3. gliteOnly(3) - G992.2(g.lite) only 4. t1413Only(4) - T1.413 only 5. gdmtOnly(5) - G992.1,G992.3,G992.5,(g.dmt) only 6. ghs(6) - g.hs (G992.1,G992.2,G992.3,G992.4,G992.5,G992.5 is prior) 7. g992Dot1(7) - G992.1 8. g992Dot2(8) - G992.2 9. g992Dot3(9) - G992.3 10. g992Dot4(10) - G992.4 11. g992Dot5(11) - G992.5 12. adslAllOnly(12) - ADSL ALL ONLY 13. adslAndAdsl2(13) - G.992.1,G.992.3,T1.413(Not support) Default: all(1)

hwAdslLinePvcCfgTable.name: hwAdslLinePvcCfgTable
hwAdslLinePvcCfgTable.description: PVC configuration table of the ADSL port. The indexes of this table are ifIndex,hwAdsllinePvcVpi,and hwAdsllinePvcVci.

hwAdslLinePvcCfgEntry.name: hwAdslLinePvcCfgEntry
hwAdslLinePvcCfgEntry.description: PVC configuration table of the ADSL port. The indexes of this entry are ifIndex,hwAdsllinePvcVpi,and hwAdsllinePvcVci.

hwAdslLinePvcVlanIdCfg.name: hwAdslLinePvcVlanIdCfg
hwAdslLinePvcVlanIdCfg.description: The VLAN ID of the adsl line PVC. Range: 1-4000

hwAdslLinePvcPriorityCfg.name: hwAdslLinePvcPriorityCfg
hwAdslLinePvcPriorityCfg.description: The Priority value of the adsl line PVC. Range: 0-7 Default: 0

hwAdslLinePvcDsBandCfg.name: hwAdslLinePvcDsBandCfg
hwAdslLinePvcDsBandCfg.description: The down stream band of the adsl line PVC. Range: 0-450 Default: 0

hwAdslLinePvcUsBandCfg.name: hwAdslLinePvcUsBandCfg
hwAdslLinePvcUsBandCfg.description: The up stream band of the adsl line PVC. Range: 0-450

hwAdslLinePvcMCastEnableCfg.name: hwAdslLinePvcMCastEnableCfg
hwAdslLinePvcMCastEnableCfg.description: This object allows the adsl line PVC to support multicast. Options: 1. enable(1) - Indicates that the PVC of the ADSL port is enabled to support the multicast 2. disable(2) - Indicates that the PVC of the ADSL port is disabled to support the multicast Default: disable(2)

hwAdslLinePvcIGMPEnableCfg.name: hwAdslLinePvcIGMPEnableCfg
hwAdslLinePvcIGMPEnableCfg.description: This object allows the adsl line PVC to support IGMP. Options: 1. enable(1) - Indicates that the PVC of the ADSL port is enabled to support IGMP 2. disable(2) - Indicates that the PVC of the ADSL port is disabled to support IGMP Default: disable(2)

hwAdslLinePvcIndexCfg.name: hwAdslLinePvcIndexCfg
hwAdslLinePvcIndexCfg.description: The index of the adsl line PVC. Range: 1-8

hwAdslLinePvcConnectTypeCfg.name: hwAdslLinePvcConnectTypeCfg
hwAdslLinePvcConnectTypeCfg.description: The Connected type of the adsl line PVC Options: 1. auto(0) - The Connected type of the adsl line PVC is auto 2. llc1483B(1) - The Connected type of the adsl line PVC is llc1483B 3. pppoaLLC(2) - The Connected type of the adsl line PVC is pppoaLLC 4. pppoaVcmux(3) - The Connected type of the adsl line PVC is pppoaVcmux 5. ipoaLLc(4) - The Connected type of the adsl line PVC is ipoaLLc 6. ipoaVcmux(5) - The Connected type of the adsl line PVC is ipoaVcmux

hwAdslLinePvcRowStatusCfg.name: hwAdslLinePvcRowStatusCfg
hwAdslLinePvcRowStatusCfg.description: Row status. Add or delete a table item.

hwadslLineCfgTable.name: hwadslLineCfgTable
hwadslLineCfgTable.description: This table includes common attributes describing both ends of the line. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwadslLineCfgEntry.name: hwadslLineCfgEntry
hwadslLineCfgEntry.description: This table includes common attributes describing both ends of the line. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwadslLineExtConfProfileCfg.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfileCfg
hwadslLineExtConfProfileCfg.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ADSL Extend Line Configuration Profile Table, (adslLineExtConfProfileTable), which applies to this ADSL line, and channels if applicable. NULL - indicates that there is no extend line profile bound to this port. Range: 0-32

hwadslLineDynamicProfileCfg.name: hwadslLineDynamicProfileCfg
hwadslLineDynamicProfileCfg.description: The value of this object identifies the row in the ADSL Dynamic Profile Table,which applies to this ADSL line, and channels if applicable. NULL - indicates that there is no Dynamic profile bound to this port. Range: 0-32

hwAdslLineBitAllocationInfoTable.name: hwAdslLineBitAllocationInfoTable
hwAdslLineBitAllocationInfoTable.description: This hwAdslLineBitAllocationInfoTable contains the detailed bit-allocation information for the current link. This information can be used to determine whether a given sub-carrier loop has sufficient margin to support ADSL data rates, and possibly to determine whether certain specific types of interference or line attenuation exist. The bit allocation information are only valid when the ATU-C is in the C-ACTIVE state. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwadsl2TSSiPsdMaskDsCfg.name: hwadsl2TSSiPsdMaskDsCfg
hwadsl2TSSiPsdMaskDsCfg.description: The downstream PSD mask applicable at the U-C2 reference point. This parameter is used only for G992.3 or G992.5 and it may impose PSD restrictions (breakpoints) in addition to the Limit PSD mask defined in G992.5. This is a string of 32 pairs of values in the following structure: Octets 0-1 - Index of 1st sub-carrier used in the context of a first breakpoint. Octet 2 - The PSD reduction for the sub-carrier indicated in octets 0 and 1. Octets 3-5 - Same, for a 2nd breakpoint. Octets 6-8 - Same, for a 3rd breakpoint. This architecture continues until octets 94-95, which are associated with a 32nd breakpoint. Each subcarrier index is an unsigned number in the range 1 and NSCds. Each PSD reduction value is in the range 0 (0dBm/Hz) to 255 (-127.5dBm/Hz) with steps of 0.5dBm/Hz. Valid values are in the range 0 to 190 (0 to -95dBm/Hz). When the number of breakpoints is less than 32, all remaining octets are set to the value 0. Note that the content of this object should be correlated with the sub-carriers mask and with the RFI setup.

hwadsl2TSSiPsdMaskUsCfg.name: hwadsl2TSSiPsdMaskUsCfg
hwadsl2TSSiPsdMaskUsCfg.description: The upstream PSD mask applicable at the U-C2 reference point. This parameter is used only for G992.3 or G992.5 and it may impose PSD restrictions (breakpoints) in addition to the Limit PSD mask defined in G992.5. This is a string of 32 pairs of values in the following structure: Octets 0+1 - Index of 1st sub-carrier used in the context of a first breakpoint. Octet 2 - The PSD reduction for the sub-carrier indicated in octets 0 and 1. Octets 3-5 - Same, for a 2nd breakpoint. Octets 6-8 - Same, for a 3rd breakpoint. This architecture continues until octets 9-11, which are associated with a fourth breakpoint. Each subcarrier index is an unsigned number in the range 1 and NSCus. Each PSD reduction value is in the range 0 (0dBm/Hz) to 255 (-127.5dBm/Hz) with steps of 0.5dBm/Hz. Valid values are in the range 0 to 190 (0 to -95dBm/Hz). When the number of breakpoints is less than 4, all remaining octets are set to the value 0. Note that the content of this object should be correlated with the sub-carriers mask and with the RFI setup.

hwadslLConfProfAdslModeCfg.name: hwadslLConfProfAdslModeCfg
hwadslLConfProfAdslModeCfg.description: The ADSL2 management model specified includes an ADSL Mode attribute which identifies an instance of ADSL Mode-Specific PSD Configuration object in the ADSL Line Profile. The following classes of ADSL operating mode are defined. Options: 1. defMode(1) - ADSL transmit mode is defMode 2. adsl(2) - ADSL transmit mode is adsl 3. adsl2Pots(3) - ADSL transmit mode is adsl2Pots 4. adsl2Isdn(4) - ADSL transmit mode is adsl2Isdn 5. adsl2PlusPots(5) - ADSL transmit mode is adsl2PlusPots 6. adsl2PlusIsdn(6) - ADSL transmit mode is adsl2PlusIsdn 7. adsl2ReachExtended(7) - ADSL transmit mode is adsl2ReachExtended 8. invalidValue(-1) - Invalid value

hwadslLineExtConfProfileRowStatusCfg.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfileRowStatusCfg
hwadslLineExtConfProfileRowStatusCfg.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table. A profile activated by setting this object to 'active'. When 'active' is set, the system will validate the profile. Before a profile can be deleted or taken out of service, (by setting this object to 'destroy' or 'outOfService') it must be first unreferenced from all associated lines. If the implementator of this MIB has chosen not to implement 'dynamic assignment' of profiles, this object's MIN-ACCESS is read-only and its value is always to be 'active'.

hwadsl2L2ModeL2TimeCfg.name: hwadsl2L2ModeL2TimeCfg
hwadsl2L2ModeL2TimeCfg.description: This minimum time (in seconds) between an entry into the L2 state and the first power trim in the L2 state and between two consecutive power trims in the L2 State. It ranges from 0 to 255 seconds. Range: 0-255 Default: 30 Unit: seconds

hwadslLineExtConfProfRtxModeDs.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfRtxModeDs
hwadslLineExtConfProfRtxModeDs.description: The mode of operation of G.998.4 retransmission in downstream direction. Options: 1. forbidden(0) - G.998.4 retransmission not allowed. 2. preferred(1) - G.998.4 retransmission is preferred. 3. forced(2) - Force the use of the G.998.4 retransmission. 4. testmode(3) - Force the use of the G.998.4 retransmission in test mode.

hwadslLineExtConfProfLeftrThreshDs.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfLeftrThreshDs
hwadslLineExtConfProfLeftrThreshDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the threshold for declaring a near-end leftr defect. The value is coded as a fraction of the NDR with valid range from 0.01 to 0.99 with increments of 0.01. A special value means the ETR shall be used as the default threshold for declaring a leftr defect.

hwadslLineExtConfProfMinEtrRtxDs.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfMinEtrRtxDs
hwadslLineExtConfProfMinEtrRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum expected throughput for the bearer channel.The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

hwadslLineExtConfProfMaxEtrRtxDs.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfMaxEtrRtxDs
hwadslLineExtConfProfMaxEtrRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the maxmum expected throughput for the bearer channel.The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

hwadslLineExtConfProfMaxNdrRtxDs.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfMaxNdrRtxDs
hwadslLineExtConfProfMaxNdrRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the maximum net data rate for the bearer channel. The values range in steps of 1000 bit/s.

hwadslLineExtConfProfMaxDelayRtxDs.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfMaxDelayRtxDs
hwadslLineExtConfProfMaxDelayRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the maximum for the instantaneous delay due to the effect of retransmission only (see G.998.4 for detailed specification). The delay ranges from 1 to 63 ms by steps of 1 ms. Unit: milliseconds

hwadslLineExtConfProfMinDelayRtxDs.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfMinDelayRtxDs
hwadslLineExtConfProfMinDelayRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum for the instantaneous delay due to the effect of retransmission only (see G.998.4 for detailed specification). The delay ranges from 0 to 63 ms by steps of 1 ms. Unit: milliseconds

hwadslLineExtConfProfMinInpShineRtxDs.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfMinInpShineRtxDs
hwadslLineExtConfProfMinInpShineRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against SHINE for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 63, inclusive. Unit: symbols

hwadslLineExtConfProfShineRatioRtxDs.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfShineRatioRtxDs
hwadslLineExtConfProfShineRatioRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the SHINE ratio (detailed definition see G.998.4). The values range from 0 to 0.100 in increments of 0.001.

hwadslLineExtConfProfMinInpReinRtxDs.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfMinInpReinRtxDs
hwadslLineExtConfProfMinInpReinRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the minimum impulse noise protection against REIN for the bearer channel if it is transported over DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz. The impulse noise protection is expressed in DMT symbols with a subcarrier spacing of 4.3125 kHz and can take any integer value from 0 to 7, inclusive.

hwadslLineExtConfProfIatReinRtxDs.name: hwadslLineExtConfProfIatReinRtxDs
hwadslLineExtConfProfIatReinRtxDs.description: If retransmission is used in downstream direction, this parameter specifies the inter-arrival time that shall be assumed for REIN protection. Options: 1. frequency100Hz(0) - an inter-arrival time derived from a REIN at 100 Hz 2. frequency120Hz(1) - an inter-arrival time derived from a REIN at 120 Hz

hwadsl2LExtLineProfReferenceClock.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfReferenceClock
hwadsl2LExtLineProfReferenceClock.description: This object configures the clock reference for the ATU-C in an ADSL line. Represented as an enumeration. Options: 1. freeRun(1) - Indicates the local clock 2. system(2) - Indicates the system clock

hwadsl2LExtLineProfRfiBands.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfRfiBands
hwadsl2LExtLineProfRfiBands.description: The RFI notch parameter. It is a string consist of begin tone index, end tone index. This is a string of 4 groups of values in the following structure: Octets 0+1 - Index of start sub-carrier used in the context of a first group Octets 2+3 - Index of end sub-carrier used in the context of a first group Octets 4-7 - Same, for a 2nd group This architecture continues until octets 12-15, which are associated with a 4th group.It can contain as most as 4 groups.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEPsd.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEPsd
hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEPsd.description: This parameter defines the PSD mask that is assumed to be permitted at the exchange. This parameter shall use the same format as PSDMASKds.The maximum number of breakpoints for DPBOEPSD is 16. This is a string of 16 pairs of values in the following structure: Octets 0+1 - Index of 1st sub-carrier used in the context of a first breakpoint. Octet 2 - The PSD reduction for the sub-carrier indicated in octets 0 and 1 Octets 3-5 - Same, for a 2nd breakpoint Octets 6-8 - Same, for a 3rd breakpoint This architecture continues until octets 45-47, which are associated with a 16th breakpoint. Each subcarrier index is an unsigned number in the range 1 and NSCds. Each PSD reduction value is in the range 0 (0dBm/Hz) to 255 (-127.5dBm/Hz) with steps of 0.5dBm/Hz. Valid values are in the range 0 to 190 (0 to -95dBm/Hz). When the number of breakpoints is less than 16, all remaining octets are set to the value 0xff.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEsEL.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEsEL
hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEsEL.description: This configuration parameter defines the assumed electrical length of cables (E-side cables) connecting exchange based DSL services to a remote flexibility point (cabinet), that hosts the xTU-C that is subject to spectrally shaped downstream power back-off depending on this length. For this parameter the electrical length is defined as the loss (in dB) of an equivalent length of hypothetical cable at a reference frequency defined by the network operator or in spectrum management regulations. DPBOESEL shall be coded as an unsigned integer representing an electrical length from 0 dB (coded as 0) to 255.5 dB (coded as 511) in steps of 0.5 dB. All values in the range are valid.If DPBOESEL is set to zero, the DPBO in this section shall be disabled.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEselMin.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEselMin
hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEselMin.description: DPBOESELMIN in dB is the minimum of all main cable losses for the KVz supplied when using the SOL model (expansion of a KVz and ADSL2 provision of additional KVz areas from this KVz using cross-cables to additional KVz), including the KVz at the MSAN site. This value must be adjustable as the minimum requirement via the SNMP interface in the configuration profile for each ADSL2 port, and is set individually for each MSAN site and usage. As an option, adjustment can be done for each MSAN or line card, thus taking effect for entire port groups. It is used only for determining the MUF.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEsCableModelA.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEsCableModelA
hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEsCableModelA.description: This configuration parameter defines a cable model in terms of three scalars DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB and DPBOESCMC that shall be used to describe the frequency dependent loss of E-side cables.Parameters DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB, DPBOESCMC shall be coded as unsigned integers representing a scalar value from -1 (coded as 0) to 1.5 (coded as 640) in step of 1/256. All values in the range are valid.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEsCableModelB.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEsCableModelB
hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEsCableModelB.description: This configuration parameter defines a cable model in terms of three scalars DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB and DPBOESCMC that shall be used to describe the frequency dependent loss of E-side cables.Parameters DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB, DPBOESCMC shall be coded as unsigned integers representing a scalar value from -1 (coded as 0) to 1.5 (coded as 640) in step of 1/256. All values in the range are valid.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEsCableModelC.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEsCableModelC
hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboEsCableModelC.description: This configuration parameter defines a cable model in terms of three scalars DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB and DPBOESCMC that shall be used to describe the frequency dependent loss of E-side cables.Parameters DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB, DPBOESCMC shall be coded as unsigned integers representing a scalar value from -1 (coded as 0) to 1.5 (coded as 640) in step of 1/256. All values in the range are valid.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboMus.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboMus
hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboMus.description: DPBOMUS defines the assumed minimum usable receive signal PSD (in dBm/Hz) for exchange based services, used to modify parameter DPBOFMAX defined below. It shall be coded as an unsigned integer representing a PSD level from 0 dBm/Hz (coded as 0) to -127.5 dBm/Hz (coded as 255) in steps of 0.5 dBm/Hz. All values in the range are valid.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboFMin.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboFMin
hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboFMin.description: DPBOFMIN defines the minimum frequency from which the DPBO shall be applied. It shall be coded as a 16 bits unsigned integer representing a frequency in multiple of 4.3125 KHz. The range of valid values is from 0 kHz (coded as 0) to 2203.6875 kHz (coded as 511).

hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboFMax.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboFMax
hwadsl2LExtLineProfDpboFMax.description: DPBOFMAX defines the maximum frequency at which DPBO may be applied. It shall be coded as a 16 bits unsigned integer representing a frequency in multiple of 4.3125 KHz. The range of valid values is from 138 kHz (coded as 32) to 2203.6875 kHz (coded as 511).

hwadsl2LExtLineProfMaxNomAtpDs.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfMaxNomAtpDs
hwadsl2LExtLineProfMaxNomAtpDs.description: The maximum nominal aggregate transmit power in the downstream direction during initialization and showtime. It ranges from 0 to 255 units of 0.1 dBm (physical values are 0 to 25.5 dBm).

hwadsl2LExtLineProfMaxNomAtpUs.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfMaxNomAtpUs
hwadsl2LExtLineProfMaxNomAtpUs.description: The maximum nominal aggregate transmit power in the upstream direction during initialization and showtime. It ranges from 0 to 255 units of 0.1 dBm (physical values are 0 to 25.5 dBm).

hwadsl2LExtLineProfInmIatoDs.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfInmIatoDs
hwadsl2LExtLineProfInmIatoDs.description: The parameter of downstream impulse noise monitoring inter arrival time offset. This is the inter arrival time offset that the xTU receiver shall use to determine in which bin of the inter arrival time histogram the IAT is reported. The valid values for INMIATO ranges from 3 to 511 DMT symbols in steps of 1 DMT symbol.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfInmIatsDs.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfInmIatsDs
hwadsl2LExtLineProfInmIatsDs.description: The parameter of downstream impulse noise monitoring inter arrival time step. This is the inter arrival time step that the xTU receiver shall use to determine in which bin of the inter arrival time histogram the IAT is reported. The valid values for INMIATS ranges from 0 to 7 in steps of 1.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfInmCcDs.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfInmCcDs
hwadsl2LExtLineProfInmCcDs.description: The parameter of downstream impulse noise monitoring cluster continuation value. This is the cluster continuation value that the xTU receiver shall use in the cluster indication process described in the relevant ITU-T Recommendation. The valid values for INMCC range from 0 to 64 DMT symbols in steps of 1 DMT symbol.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfInmInpeqModeDs.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfInmInpeqModeDs
hwadsl2LExtLineProfInmInpeqModeDs.description: The parameter of downstream impulse noise monitoring equivalent impulse noise protect mode. This is the INM Equivalent INP Mode that the xTU receiver shall use in the computation of the Equivalent INP, as defined in the relevant ITU-T Recommendation. The valid values for INM_INPEQ_MODE are 0, 1, 2, 3, and 4.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfForceInpDs.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfForceInpDs
hwadsl2LExtLineProfForceInpDs.description: The parameter indicates that the framer settings of the upstream bearer shall be selected such that the impulse noise protection computed according to the formula specified in the relevant recommendation is greater than or equal to the minimal impulse noise protection requirement. This flag shall have the same value for all the bearers of one line in the same direction.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfForceInpUs.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfForceInpUs
hwadsl2LExtLineProfForceInpUs.description: The parameter indicates that the framer settings of the upstream bearer shall be selected such that the impulse noise protection computed according to the formula specified in the relevant recommendation is greater than or equal to the minimal impulse noise protection requirement. This flag shall have the same value for all the bearers of one line in the same direction.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfInitPolicy.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfInitPolicy
hwadsl2LExtLineProfInitPolicy.description: If retransmission is not used in a given transmit direction, this parameter indicates which policy shall be applied to determine the transceiver configuration parameters at initialization. The valid values for CIPOLICY are 0,1 and 2. Those policies are defined in the respective recommendations. Options: 1. policy0 (1) - Policy 0 according to the applicable standard 2. policy1 (2) - Policy 1 according to the applicable standard 3. policy2 (3) - Policy 2 according to the applicable standard

hwadsl2LExtLineProfL3Time.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfL3Time
hwadsl2LExtLineProfL3Time.description: This minimum time (in seconds) between an entry into the L3 state and the L0 or L2 state.

hwadsl2LExtLineProfL3ModeState.name: hwadsl2LExtLineProfL3ModeState
hwadsl2LExtLineProfL3ModeState.description: Power management state enabling. The state of L3 power management mode. Options: 1. enabled(1) - The L3 power management mode is enabled 2. disabled(2) - The L3 power management mode is disabled

hwAdslLineLatestActParaInfoTable.name: hwAdslLineLatestActParaInfoTable
hwAdslLineLatestActParaInfoTable.description: This table provides one row for each ADSL port. Each row contains the latest actived parameters. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwAdslLineLatestActParaInfoEntry.name: hwAdslLineLatestActParaInfoEntry
hwAdslLineLatestActParaInfoEntry.description: This table provides one row for each ADSL port. Each row contains the latest actived parameters. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwAdslLineLatestDeactiveTimeInfo.name: hwAdslLineLatestDeactiveTimeInfo
hwAdslLineLatestDeactiveTimeInfo.description: Actual time when latest deactived. If port is actived, the value is invalid.

hwAdslAtucLatestTxRateInfo.name: hwAdslAtucLatestTxRateInfo
hwAdslAtucLatestTxRateInfo.description: Actual transmit rate on this channel when latest actived. Unit: bps

hwAdslAturLatestTxRateInfo.name: hwAdslAturLatestTxRateInfo
hwAdslAturLatestTxRateInfo.description: Actual transmit rate on this channel when latest actived. Unit: bps

hwAdslAtucLatestSnrMgnInfo.name: hwAdslAtucLatestSnrMgnInfo
hwAdslAtucLatestSnrMgnInfo.description: Noise Margin as seen by this ATU-C at the time of the last adslAtucRateChangeTrap event. Unit: tenth dB.

hwAdslAturLatestSnrMgnInfo.name: hwAdslAturLatestSnrMgnInfo
hwAdslAturLatestSnrMgnInfo.description: Noise Margin as seen by this ATU-R at the time of the last adslAtucRateChangeTrap event. Unit: tenth dB.

hwAdslAtucLatestAtnInfo.name: hwAdslAtucLatestAtnInfo
hwAdslAtucLatestAtnInfo.description: Measured difference in the total power transmitted as seen by this ATU-C at the time of the last adslAtucRateChangeTrap event. Unit: tenth dB.

hwAdslAturLatestAtnInfo.name: hwAdslAturLatestAtnInfo
hwAdslAturLatestAtnInfo.description: Measured difference in the total power transmitted as seen by this ATU-R at the time of the last adslAtucRateChangeTrap event. Unit: tenth dB.

hwAdslAtucLatestAttainableRateInfo.name: hwAdslAtucLatestAttainableRateInfo
hwAdslAtucLatestAttainableRateInfo.description: Indicates the maximum attainable data rate by the ATU-C at the time of the last adslAtucRateChangeTrap event. Unit: bps

hwAdslAturLatestAttainableRateInfo.name: hwAdslAturLatestAttainableRateInfo
hwAdslAturLatestAttainableRateInfo.description: Indicates the maximum attainable data rate by the ATU-R at the time of the last adslAtucRateChangeTrap event. Unit: bps

hwAdslAtucLatestConfTxRateInfo.name: hwAdslAtucLatestConfTxRateInfo
hwAdslAtucLatestConfTxRateInfo.description: Configured transmit rate for ADSL port. See adslAtucConfRateChanRatio for information regarding RADSL mode and ATUR transmit rate for ATUC receive rates. Unit: bps.

hwAdslAturLatestConfTxRateInfo.name: hwAdslAturLatestConfTxRateInfo
hwAdslAturLatestConfTxRateInfo.description: Configured receive rate for ADSL port. See adslAtucConfRateChanRatio for information regarding RADSL mode and ATUR transmit rate for ATUC receive rates. Unit: bps.

hwAdslAtucLatestInterleaveDelayInfo.name: hwAdslAtucLatestInterleaveDelayInfo
hwAdslAtucLatestInterleaveDelayInfo.description: Interleave delay for this channel when latest actived. Unit: milliseconds

hwAdslAturLatestInterleaveDelayInfo.name: hwAdslAturLatestInterleaveDelayInfo
hwAdslAturLatestInterleaveDelayInfo.description: Interleave delay for this channel when latest actived. Unit: milliseconds

hwAdslAtucLatestTargetSnrMgnInfo.name: hwAdslAtucLatestTargetSnrMgnInfo
hwAdslAtucLatestTargetSnrMgnInfo.description: Port Signal/Noise Margin. Range: 0-310 Unit: tenth dB

hwAdslAturLatestTargetSnrMgnInfo.name: hwAdslAturLatestTargetSnrMgnInfo
hwAdslAturLatestTargetSnrMgnInfo.description: Port Signal/Noise Margin. Range: 0-310 Unit: tenth dB

hwAdslAtucLatestTxRateThresholdInfo.name: hwAdslAtucLatestTxRateThresholdInfo
hwAdslAtucLatestTxRateThresholdInfo.description: Port down stream threshold. Unit: bps

hwAdslAturLatestTxRateThresholdInfo.name: hwAdslAturLatestTxRateThresholdInfo
hwAdslAturLatestTxRateThresholdInfo.description: Port up stream threshold. Unit: bps

hwXdslPortPerformanceStatInfoTable.name: hwXdslPortPerformanceStatInfoTable
hwXdslPortPerformanceStatInfoTable.description: XDSL port performance staticstic table. The indexes of this table are ifIndex and hwXdslPort15minutesPerformanceIntervalInfo.

hwXdslPortPerformanceStatInfoEntry.name: hwXdslPortPerformanceStatInfoEntry
hwXdslPortPerformanceStatInfoEntry.description: XDSL port performance staticstic table. The indexes of this entry are ifIndex and hwXdslPort15minutesPerformanceIntervalInfo.

hwXdslPort15minutesPerformanceIntervalIn.name: hwXdslPort15minutesPerformanceIntervalInfo
hwXdslPort15minutesPerformanceIntervalIn.description: The index of the interval which is queried. Range: 0-96

hwXdslPort15minutesPerformanceInBytesInf.name: hwXdslPort15minutesPerformanceInBytesInfo
hwXdslPort15minutesPerformanceInBytesInf.description: Read the receive bytes of xDSL port during 15 minutes.

hwXdslPort15minutesPerformanceOutBytesIn.name: hwXdslPort15minutesPerformanceOutBytesInfo
hwXdslPort15minutesPerformanceOutBytesIn.description: Read the transmit bytes of xDSL port during 15 minutes.

hwXdslPortSyncSuccNumberInfo.name: hwXdslPortSyncSuccNumberInfo
hwXdslPortSyncSuccNumberInfo.description: Number of successful activations of the ADSL/G.SHDSL port within 15 minutes

hwXdslPortSyncFailNumberInfo.name: hwXdslPortSyncFailNumberInfo
hwXdslPortSyncFailNumberInfo.description: Number of failed activations of the ADSL/G.SHDSL port within 15 minutes

hwXdslPortAtucCodeViolationInfo.name: hwXdslPortAtucCodeViolationInfo
hwXdslPortAtucCodeViolationInfo.description: Number of head errors of the ATUC cell within 15 minutes.

hwXdslPortAturCodeViolationInfo.name: hwXdslPortAturCodeViolationInfo
hwXdslPortAturCodeViolationInfo.description: Number of head errors of the ATUR cell within 15 minutes.

hwXdslPortAtucFecSecondsInfo.name: hwXdslPortAtucFecSecondsInfo
hwXdslPortAtucFecSecondsInfo.description: Seconds of the ATUC FEC errors within 15 minutes.

hwXdslPortAturFecSecondsInfo.name: hwXdslPortAturFecSecondsInfo
hwXdslPortAturFecSecondsInfo.description: Seconds of the ATUR FEC errors within 15 minutes.

hwXdslPortCurrent15minutesStatTimeInfo.name: hwXdslPortCurrent15minutesStatTimeInfo
hwXdslPortCurrent15minutesStatTimeInfo.description: Read the Stat. time of current 15 minutes.

hwadslAtucPhysInfoTable.name: hwadslAtucPhysInfoTable
hwadslAtucPhysInfoTable.description: This table provides the physical layer parameters of each ATUC. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwadslAtucPhysInfoEntry.name: hwadslAtucPhysInfoEntry
hwadslAtucPhysInfoEntry.description: This table provides the physical layer parameters of each ATUC. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwAdslAtucCurrTransModeInfo.name: hwAdslAtucCurrTransModeInfo
hwAdslAtucCurrTransModeInfo.description: A set of ADSL line transmission modes.

hwAdslAtucCurrSignalAtnInfo.name: hwAdslAtucCurrSignalAtnInfo
hwAdslAtucCurrSignalAtnInfo.description: Current signal attenuation of the ATU-C, indicating the difference between the transmit signal of the ATU-R and the receive signal of the ATU-C. Range: 0-630 Unit: tenth dB

hwadslAtucInvG994VendorId.name: hwadslAtucInvG994VendorId
hwadslAtucInvG994VendorId.description: The ATU G.994.1 Vendor ID as inserted in the G.994.1 CL/CLR message. It consists of 8 binary octets, including a country code followed by a (regionally allocated) provider code, as defined in Recommendation T.35.

hwadslAtucLInvSelfTestResult.name: hwadslAtucLInvSelfTestResult
hwadslAtucLInvSelfTestResult.description: The ATU self-test result, coded as a 32-bit value. The most significant octet of the result is '0' if the self-test passed, and '1' if the self-test failed. The interpretation of the other octets is vendor discretionary.

hwadslAtucTransmissionCapabilitiesInfo.name: hwadslAtucTransmissionCapabilitiesInfo
hwadslAtucTransmissionCapabilitiesInfo.description: The ATU transmission system capability list of the different coding types. It is coded in a bit-map representation with 1 or more bits set. A bit set to '1' means that the ATU supports the respective coding. The value may be derived from the handshaking procedures defined in G.994.1.

hwadslLineExtInfoTable.name: hwadslLineExtInfoTable
hwadslLineExtInfoTable.description: This table is an extension of RFC 2662. It contains ADSL line configuration and monitoring information. This includes the ADSL line's capabilities and actual ADSL transmission system. An entry extends the adslLineEntry defined in [RFC2662]. Each entry corresponds to an ADSL line. The index of this table is ifIndex.

hwadslLineExtInfoEntry.name: hwadslLineExtInfoEntry
hwadslLineExtInfoEntry.description: This table is an extension of RFC 2662. It contains ADSL line configuration and monitoring information. This includes the ADSL line's capabilities and actual ADSL transmission system. An entry extends the adslLineEntry defined in [RFC2662]. Each entry corresponds to an ADSL line. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwadsl2LineTransAtucActualInfo.name: hwadsl2LineTransAtucActualInfo
hwadsl2LineTransAtucActualInfo.description: The actual transmission mode of the ATU-C. During ADSL line initialization, the ADSL Transceiver Unit - Remote terminal end (ATU-R) will determine the mode used for the link. This value will be limited a single transmission mode that is a subset of those modes enabled by the ATU-C and denoted by adslLineTransAtucConfig. After an initialization has occurred, its mode is saved as the 'Current' mode and is persistence should the link go down. This object returns 0 (i.e. BITS with no mode bit set) if the mode is not known.

hwadslLineStatusRtxUsedDs.name: hwadslLineStatusRtxUsedDs

hwadslLineAlarmConfProfileCfgTable.description: This table contains information on the ADSL line configuration. One entry in this table reflects a profile defined by a manager which can be used to configure the modem for a physical line. The entry contains information on the ADSL line configuration. Each entry consists of a list of parameters that represents the configuration of an ADSL modem. When 'dynamic' profiles are implemented, a default profile will always exist. This profile's name will be set to 'DEFVAL' and its parameters will be set to vendor specific values, unless otherwise specified in this document. When 'static' profiles are implemented, profiles are automatically created or destroyed as ADSL physical lines are discovered and removed by the system. The name of the profile will be equivalent to the decimal value of the line's interface index. The index of this table is adslLineAlarmConfProfileName.

hwadslPortRateChangeTrapParaInfoEntry.description: ADSL line rate change trap parameter table. The index of this entry is ifIndex.

hwAdsl2SCStatusInfoEntry.name: hwAdsl2SCStatusInfoEntry
hwAdsl2SCStatusInfoEntry.description: The table hwAdsl2SCStatusInfoTable contains status parameters of the ADSL2 sub-carriers. The indexes of this entry are ifIndex and hwAdsl2SCStatusDirectionInfo.

hwAdsl2SCStatusDirectionInfo.name: hwAdsl2SCStatusDirectionInfo
hwAdsl2SCStatusDirectionInfo.description: The direction of the sub-carrier is either upstream or downstream. Options: 1. upstream(1) - The direction of the sub-carrier is upstream 2. downstream(2) - The direction of the sub-carrier is downstream

hwAdsl2SCStatusSnrInfo.name: hwAdsl2SCStatusSnrInfo
hwAdsl2SCStatusSnrInfo.description: The SNR Margin per sub-carrier, expressing the ratio between the received signal power and received noise power per subscriber. It is an array of 512 octets, designed for supporting up to 512 (downstream) sub-carriers. The number of utilized octets on downstream direction depends on NSCds, and on upstream direction it depends on NSCus. This value is referred to here as NSC. Octet i (0 <= i < NSC) is set to a value in the range 0 to 254 to indicate that the respective downstream or upstream sub- carrier i has SNR of: (-32 + Adsl2SubcarrierSnr(i)/2) in dB (i.e., -32 to 95dB). The special value 255 means that no measurement could be done for the subcarrier because it is out of the PSD mask passband or that the noise PSD is out of range to be represented. Each value in this array is 8 bits wide.

hwAdsl2SCStatusBitsAllocInfo.name: hwAdsl2SCStatusBitsAllocInfo
hwAdsl2SCStatusBitsAllocInfo.description: The bits allocation per sub-carrier. An array of 256 octets (512 nibbles), designed for supporting up to 512 (downstream) sub-carriers. The number of utilized nibbles on downstream direction depends on NSCds, and on upstream direction it depends on NSCus. This value is referred to here as NSC. Nibble i (0 <= i < NSC) is set to a value in the range 0 to 15 to indicate that the respective downstream or upstream sub-carrier i has the same amount of bits allocation.

hwAdsl2SCStatusGainAllocInfo.name: hwAdsl2SCStatusGainAllocInfo
hwAdsl2SCStatusGainAllocInfo.description: The gain allocation per sub-carrier. An array of 512 16-bits values, designed for supporting up to 512 (downstream) sub- carriers. The number of utilized octets on downstream direction depends on NSCds, and on upstream direction it depends on NSCus. This value is referred to here as NSC. Value i (0 <= i < NSC) is in the range 0 to 4093 to indicate that the respective downstream or upstream sub-carrier i has the same amount of gain value. The gain value is represented as a multiple of 1/512 on a linear scale. Each value in this array is 16 bits wide and is stored in big endian format.

hwAdsl2SCStatusLogInfo.name: hwAdsl2SCStatusLogInfo
hwAdsl2SCStatusLogInfo.description: An array of up to 512 real H(f) logarithmic representation values in dB for the respective transmission direction. It is designed to support up to 512 (downstream) sub-carriers. The number of utilized values on downstream direction depends on NSCds, and on upstream direction it depends on NSCus. This value is referred to here as NSC. Each array entry represents the real Hlog(f = i*Df) value for a particular sub-carrier index i, (0 <= i < NSC). The real Hlog(f) value is represented as (6-m(i)/10), with m(i) in the range 0 to 1022. A special value m=1023 indicates that no measurement could be done for the subcarrier because it is out of the passband or that the attenuation is out of range to be represented. This parameter is applicable in loop diagnostic procedure and initialization. Each value in this array is 16 bits wide and is stored in big endian format.

hwAdsl2SCStatusQlnInfo.name: hwAdsl2SCStatusQlnInfo
hwAdsl2SCStatusQlnInfo.description: An array of up to 512 real Quiet Line Noise values in dBm/Hz for the respective transmission direction. It is designed for up to 512 (downstream) sub-carriers. The number of utilized values on downstream direction depends on NSCds, and on upstream direction it depends on NSCus. This value is referred to here as NSC. Each array entry represents the QLN(f = i*Df) value for a particular sub-carrier index i, (0 <= i < NSC). The QLN(f) is represented as (-23-n(i)/2), with n(i) in the range 0 to 254. A special value n(i)=255 indicates that no measurement could be done for the subcarrier because it is out of the passband or that the noise PSD is out of range to be represented. This parameter is applicable in loop diagnostic procedure and initialization. Each value in this array is 8 bits wide.

hwAdsl2SCStatusSnrMarginInfo.name: hwAdsl2SCStatusSnrMarginInfo
hwAdsl2SCStatusSnrMarginInfo.description: SNR Margin is the maximum increase in dB of the noise power received at the ATU (ATU-R on downstream direction and ATU-C on upstream direction), such that the BER requirements are met for all bearer channels received at the ATU. It ranges from -640 to 630 units of 0.1 dB (physical values are -64 to 63 dB).

hwAdsl2SCStatusTxPSDInfo.name: hwAdsl2SCStatusTxPSDInfo
hwAdsl2SCStatusTxPSDInfo.description: The PSD MASK per sub-carrier. An array of 512 16-bits values, designed for supporting up to 512 (downstream) sub-carriers. It ranges from -1400 to -300 units of 0.1 dBm/Hz (physical values are -140 to -30 dBm/Hz)

hwxdslDynamicProfPmModeCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfPmModeCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfPmModeCfg.description: Power management state Enabling. Defines the power states the xTU-C or xTU-R may autonomously transition to on this line. The various bit positions are: allowTransitionsToIdle (0) and allowTransitionsToLowPower (1). A bit with a '1' value means that the xTU is allowed to transit into the respective state and a '0' value means that the xTU is not allowed to transit into the respective state.

hwxdslDynamicProfL0TimeCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfL0TimeCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfL0TimeCfg.description: This minimum time (in seconds) between an exit from the L2 state and the next Entry into the L2 state. It ranges from 0 to 255 seconds. Range: 0-255

hwxdslDynamicProfL2TimeCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfL2TimeCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfL2TimeCfg.description: This minimum time (in seconds) between an entry into the L2 state and the first power trim in the L2 state and between two consecutive power trims in the L2 State. It ranges from 0 to 255 seconds. Range: 0-255

hwxdslDynamicProfL2AtprCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfL2AtprCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfL2AtprCfg.description: The maximum aggregate transmit power reduction (in dB) that can be performed at transition of L0 to L2 state or through a single power trim in the L2 state. It ranges from 0 dB to 31 dB. Range: 0-31 Unit: dB

hwxdslDynamicProfL2AtprtCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfL2AtprtCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfL2AtprtCfg.description: The total maximum aggregate transmit power reduction (in dB) that can be performed in an L2 state. This is the sum of all reductions of L2 Request (i.e., at transition of L0 to L2 state) and power trims. Range: 0-31 Unit: dB

hwxdslDynamicProfDpboEPsdCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfDpboEPsdCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfDpboEPsdCfg.description: This parameter defines the PSD mask that is assumed to be permitted at the exchange. This parameter shall use the same format as PSDMASKds. The maximum number of breakpoints for DPBOEPSD is 16. This is a string of 16 pairs of values in the following structure: Octets 0+1 - Index of 1st sub-carrier used in the context of a first breakpoint. Octet 2 - The PSD reduction for the sub-carrier indicated in octets 0 and 1. Octets 3-5 - Same, for a 2nd breakpoint. Octets 6-8 - Same, for a 3rd breakpoint. This architecture continues until octets 45-47, which are associated with a 16th breakpoint. Each subcarrier index is an unsigned number in the range 1 and NSCds. Each PSD reduction value is in the range 0 (0dBm/Hz) to 255 (-127.5dBm/Hz) with steps of 0.5dBm/Hz. Valid values are in the range 0 to 190 (0 to -95dBm/Hz). When the number of breakpoints is less than 16, all remaining octets are set to the value 0xff.

hwxdslDynamicProfDpboEsELCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfDpboEsELCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfDpboEsELCfg.description: This configuration parameter defines the assumed electrical length of cables (E-side cables) connecting exchange based DSL services to a remote flexibility point (cabinet), that hosts the xTU-C that is subject to spectrally shaped downstream power back-off depending on this length. For this parameter the electrical length is defined as the loss (in dB) of an equivalent length of hypothetical cable at a reference frequency defined by the network operator or in spectrum management regulations. DPBOESEL shall be coded as an unsigned integer representing an electrical length from 0 dB (coded as 0) to 255.5 dB (coded as 511) in steps of 0.5 dB. All values in the range are valid.If DPBOESEL is set to zero, the DPBO in this section shall be disabled. Range: 0-511 Unit: 0.5dB

hwxdslDynamicProfDpboEscmCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfDpboEscmCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfDpboEscmCfg.description: This configuration parameter defines a cable model in terms of three scalars DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB and DPBOESCMC that shall be used to describe the frequency dependent loss of E-side cables.Parameters DPBOESCMA, DPBOESCMB, DPBOESCMC shall be coded as unsigned integers representing a scalar value from -1 (coded as 0) to 1.5 (coded as 640) in step of 1/256. All values in the range are valid. Octets 0+1 DPBOESCMA Octets 2+3 DPBOESCMB Octets 4+5 DPBOESCMC

hwxdslDynamicProfDpboMusCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfDpboMusCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfDpboMusCfg.description: DPBOMUS defines the assumed Minimum Usable receive Signal PSD (in dBm/Hz) for exchange based services, used to modify parameter DPBOFMAX defined below. It shall be coded as an unsigned integer representing a PSD level from 0 dBm/Hz (coded as 0) to -127.5 dBm/Hz (coded as 255) in steps of 0.5 dBm/Hz. All values in the range are valid. Range: 0-255 Unit: 0.5dBm/Hz

hwxdslDynamicProfDpboFMinCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfDpboFMinCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfDpboFMinCfg.description: DPBOFMIN defines the minimum frequency from which the DPBO shall be applied. It shall be coded as a 16 bits unsigned integer representing a frequency in multiple of 4.3125 KHz. The range of valid values is from 0 kHz (coded as 0) to 8832 kHz (coded as 2048). Range: 0-2048 Unit: 4.3125 KHz

hwxdslDynamicProfDpboFMaxCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfDpboFMaxCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfDpboFMaxCfg.description: DPBOFMAX defines the maximum frequency at which DPBO may be applied. It shall be coded as a 16 bits unsigned integer representing a frequency in multiple of 4.3125 KHz. The range of valid values is from 138 kHz (coded as 32) to 29997.75 kHz (coded as 6956). Range: 32-6956 Unit: 4.3125 KHz

hwxdslDynamicProfUpboPsdBandCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfUpboPsdBandCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfUpboPsdBandCfg.description: This parameter defines the UPBO reference PSD used to compute the upstream power back-off for each upstream band except US0. A UPBOPSD defined for each band ahsll consist of two parameters [a, b]. Parameter a shall be coded as an unsigned 12-bit number from 40 dBm/Hz (coded as 0) to 80.95 dBm/Hz (coded as 4095) in steps of 0.01 dBm/Hz; and b shall be coded as an unsigned 12 bit number from 0 (coded as 0) to 40.95 dBm/Hz (coded as 4095) in steps of 0.01 dBm/Hz. The UPBO reference PSD at the frequency f expressed in MHz shall be equal to '-a-b(SQRT(f))'. The set of parameter values a = 40 dBm/Hz, b = 0 dBm/Hz is a special configuration to disable UPBO in the respective upstream band. Octets 0+1 - a[0] Octets 2+3 - b[0] Octets 4+5 - a[1] Octets 6+7 - b[1] Octets 8+9 - a[2] Octets 10+11 - b[2] Octets 12+13 - a[3] Octets 14+15 - b[3]

hwxdslDynamicProfUpboKLFCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfUpboKLFCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfUpboKLFCfg.description: This parameter is a flag that forces the VTU-R to use the electrical loop length of the CO-MIB (UPBOKL) to compute the UPBO. The value shall be forced if the flag is set to 1. Otherwise, the electrical loop length shall be autonomously selected by the VTU-O. Options: 1. forced(1) - Force the CPE to use the electrical length of the CO(UPBOKL) to compute the UPBO 2. auto(2) - Electrical length shall be autonomously selected by the CO 3. invalidValue(-1) - Invalid value

hwxdslDynamicProfUpboKLCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfUpboKLCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfUpboKLCfg.description: This parameter defines the electrical loop length expressed in dB at 1MHz, kl0, configured by the CO-MIB. The value shall be coded as an unsigned 16 bit number in the range 0 (coded as 0) to 128 dB (coded as 1280) in steps of 0.1 dB. Range: 0-1280 Unit: 0.1 dB

hwxdslDynamicProfRfiBandsCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfRfiBandsCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfRfiBandsCfg.description: The subset of PSD mask breakpoints that shall be used to notch an RFI band. It is a string of bands consist of begin tone index and end tone index. for example :0-10,20-50,100-4095 It can contain as most as 16 bands.

hwxdslDynamicProfToneBlackOutCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfToneBlackOutCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfToneBlackOutCfg.description: The subset of subcarriermask that shall be used to mask the subcarriers. It is a string of bands consist of begin tone index and end tone index. For example :0-10,20-50,100-4095. It can contain as most as 8 bands.

hwxdslDynamicProfCarMaskDSCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfCarMaskDSCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfCarMaskDSCfg.description: Sub-carriers mask. A bitmap of 512 bits that allows masking up to 512 downstream sub-carriers, depending on NSCds. If bit i (0 <= i < NSCds) is set to '1', the respective downstream sub-carrier i is masked, and if set to '0', the respective sub-carrier is unmasked. Note that there should always be unmasked sub-carriers (i.e., the object cannot be all 1's). Also note that if NSCds < 512, all bits i (NSCds i <= 512) should be set to '1'.

hwxdslDynamicProfCarMaskUSCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfCarMaskUSCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfCarMaskUSCfg.description: Sub-carriers mask. A bitmap of 64 bits that allows masking up to 64 downstream sub-carriers, depending on NSCds. If bit i (0 <= i < NSCus) is set to '1', the respective upstream sub-carrier i is masked, and if set to '0', the respective sub-carrier is unmasked. Note that there should always be unmasked sub-carriers (i.e., the object cannot be all 1's). Also note that if NSCus < 64, all bits i (NSCus < i <= 64) should be set to '1'.

hwxdslDynamicProfPsdMaskDsCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfPsdMaskDsCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfPsdMaskDsCfg.description: This configuration parameter defines the downstream PSD mask applicable at the U C2 reference point. This MIB PSD mask may impose PSD restrictions in addition to the Limit PSD mask defined in the relevant Recommendation (e.g., G.992.5, G.993.2). This is a string of 32 pairs of values in the following structure: Octets 0+1 - Index of 1st sub-carrier used in the context of a first breakpoint. Octet 2 - The PSD reduction for the sub-carrier indicated in octets 0 and 1. Octets 3-5 - Same, for a 2nd breakpoint. Octets 6-8 - Same, for a 3rd breakpoint. This architecture continues until octets 94-95, which are associated with a 32nd breakpoint. Each subcarrier index is an unsigned number in the range 0 and (NSCds - 1). Each PSD reduction value is in the range 0 (0dBm/Hz) to 255 (-127.5dBm/Hz) with steps of 0.5dBm/Hz. Valid values are in the range 0 to 190 (0 to -95dBm/Hz). When the number of breakpoints is less than 32, all remaining octets are set to the value 0xff. Note that the content of this object should be correlated with the sub-carriers mask and with the RFI setup.

hwxdslDynamicProfPsdMaskUsCfg.name: hwxdslDynamicProfPsdMaskUsCfg
hwxdslDynamicProfPsdMaskUsCfg.description: This configuration parameter defines the upstream PSD mask applicable at the U R2 reference point. This MIB PSD mask may impose PSD restrictions in addition to the Limit PSD mask defined in the relevant Recommendations (e.g., ITU-T Recommendations G.992.3, G.993.2). This is a string of 16 pairs of values in the following structure: Octets 0+1 - Index of 1st sub-carrier used in the context of a first breakpoint. Octet 2 - The PSD reduction for the sub-carrier indicated in octets 0 and 1. Octets 3-5 - Same, for a 2nd breakpoint. Octets 45-47 - Same, for a 3rd breakpoint. This architecture continues until octets 45-47, which are associated with a 16th breakpoint. Each subcarrier index is an unsigned number in the range 0 and (NSCus - 1). Each PSD reduction value is in the range 0 (0dBm/Hz) to 255 (-127.5dBm/Hz) with steps of 0.5dBm/Hz. Valid values are in the range 0 to 190 (0 to -95dBm/Hz). When the number of breakpoints is less than 16, all remaining octets are set to the value 0xff. Note that the content of this object should be correlated with the sub-carriers mask and with the RFI setup.
